# Async Effect Patterns

## AbortController for Async Operations

Async work in `useEffect` should be cancellable to avoid race conditions, state updates on unmounted components, and memory leaks.

```typescript
// ✅ Use this pattern
useEffect(() => {
  const controller = new AbortController();

  const fetchData = async () => {
    try {
      const result = await api.getData({ signal: controller.signal });
      setData(result);
    } catch (err) {
      if (!controller.signal.aborted) {
        setError(err as Error);
      }
    }
  };

  fetchData();
  return () => controller.abort();
}, [dependency]);
```

## Loading and Error State

```typescript
const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);
const [error, setError] = useState<Error | null>(null);

useEffect(() => {
  const controller = new AbortController();

  const fetchData = async () => {
    setIsLoading(true);
    setError(null);
    try {
      const result = await api.getData({ signal: controller.signal });
      setData(result);
    } catch (err) {
      if (!controller.signal.aborted) setError(err as Error);
    } finally {
      if (!controller.signal.aborted) setIsLoading(false);
    }
  };

  fetchData();
  return () => controller.abort();
}, [dependency]);
```

## Debounced Effects

Clear timeout and abort in cleanup:

```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  const controller = new AbortController();
  const timeoutId = setTimeout(async () => {
    try {
      const result = await api.search(query, { signal: controller.signal });
      setResults(result);
    } catch (err) {
      if (!controller.signal.aborted) setError(err as Error);
    }
  }, 300);

  return () => {
    clearTimeout(timeoutId);
    controller.abort();
  };
}, [query]);
```

## Anti-patterns to Avoid

```typescript
// ❌ No cleanup — can set state after unmount
useEffect(() => {
  fetchData().then(setData);
}, []);

// ❌ Async function directly in useEffect (React warning)
useEffect(async () => {
  const data = await fetchData();
  setData(data);
}, []);

// ❌ catch that runs on abort — check controller.signal.aborted before setError
```
